===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally {{zh-l|*臱}}. {{Han compound|辵|臱|alt1=辶|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=walking; movement}}. The semantic component {{zh-l|*辵}} (now {{zh-l|*辶}}) was added during bronze inscriptions.

===Etymology 1===
Perhaps cognate with {{och-l|偏|side; oblique}}, {{och-l|片|partial; one-sided}}, {{och-l|諞|glib-tongued; insincere}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Based on Old Vietnamese data, {{zh-ref|Gong (2019)}} proposes the additional preinitial *''tə-'' to the Baxter-Sagart reconstruction.

; “to have hot pot”
: From {{zh-l|邊爐|hot pot}}. Compare {{zh-l|*啤|to drink beer}}, from {{zh-l|*啤酒|beer}}.

